  <num>45-606</num>
  <heading>Oath to include affirmation.</heading>
  <text>Wherever an oath is required, an affirmation in judicial form, if made by a person conscientiously scrupulous about taking an oath, shall be deemed a sufficient compliance.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 56-2-ch854" path="">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1189, ch. 854</annotation>
